The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      BRIEFS
                  
	Howrah, Aug. 21: A nine-year-old boy died and four people were injured after a motorcycle-borne gang allegedly hurled bombs at an Intuc office near a taxi stand at Howrah Maidan this evening.    
	Ganesh Shaw, the son of a rickshaw-puller, was watching TV with four taxi drivers when the attack took place. Intuc workers clashed with police after the incident. The workers blamed the Trinamul Congress for the attack.        
	Calcutta: Home secretary Samar Ghosh said on Saturday that the state government would move Calcutta High Court against the Central Administrative Tribunals order setting aside the promotion of four inspectors-general of police for superseding two IPS officers.        
	Calcutta: The CPM on Saturday appointed former Jadavpur MP Sujan Chakraborty the secretary of the South 24-Parganas unit of the party.         
	Calcutta: Eastern Railway will run eight special trains in its Howrah division from August 22 to August 24 on the occasion of Rakhi Purnima. While two trains will run between Howrah and Tarakeswar, six will ply between Seoraphuli and Tarakeswar.        
	Calcutta: Raju Maiti, 32, a Behala resident, died of malaria on Saturday. The driver was in coma in a hospital for the past two days.                                                                                                                                                       
